Voters will be faced with their biggest choice yet in a national election after a record number of 48 political parties met the legal requirements to contest this year’s elections, the Electoral Commission (IEC) said in a media release. This is 19 more parties than contested the 2014 national elections. The parties which will contest the national elections (in alphabetical order) are:  The deadline also saw a new record number of parties contesting all provincial elections with the largest number of parties contesting Gauteng (36) and the smallest number contesting the Northern Cape (21)  The following parties will contest the provincial elections in the Eastern Cape: 